reviews.review_text: fun bobby donna lyric flub in beat it on down goes right into happy home. sounds like fun
I love a good aud Yes there is something about a good aud. CHeck out this show. is very very good

Excellent aud, incredible Playin' Also don't miss the very well played Eyes>Wharf Rat towards the end.  I love me some good '74 aud.  The SB's from this period are crispy and clean but sound cool, dry, and flat.  Not in pitch, but tone quality, probably something to do with higher overtones being lost.  Wolf sounds so much sweeter and warmer on the audience recordings (all of Jerry's guitars from Alligator through Rosebud sound wonderful, but Tiger will always hold the top place in my heart since most of my shows were with Jerry on that guitar).
